label: DiagramElements
comment: A diagram is made up of multiple diagram objects.

label: DiagramStyle
comment: A Diagram may have a DiagramStyle.

label: orientation
comment: Coordinate system orientation of the diagram. A positive orientation gives standard “right-hand” orientation, with negative orientation indicating a “left-hand” orientation. For 2D diagrams, a positive orientation will result in X values increasing from left to right and Y values increasing from bottom to top. A negative orientation gives the “left-hand” orientation (favoured by computer graphics displays) with X values increasing from left to right and Y values increasing from top to bottom.

label: x1InitialView
comment: X coordinate of the first corner of the initial view.

label: x2InitialView
comment: X coordinate of the second corner of the initial view.

label: y1InitialView
comment: Y coordinate of the first corner of the initial view.

label: y2InitialView
comment: Y coordinate of the second corner of the initial view.

label: Diagram
comment: A diagram object is part of a diagram.

label: DiagramObjectPoints
comment: A diagram object can have 0 or more points to reflect its layout position, routing (for polylines) or boundary (for polygons).

label: DiagramObjectStyle
comment: A diagram object has a style associated that provides a reference for the style used in the originating system.

label: IdentifiedObject
comment: The domain object to which this diagram object is associated.

label: VisibilityLayers
comment: A diagram object can be part of multiple visibility layers.

label: drawingOrder
comment: The drawing order of this element. The higher the number, the later the element is drawn in sequence. This is used to ensure that elements that overlap are rendered in the correct order.

label: isPolygon
comment: Defines whether or not the diagram objects points define the boundaries of a polygon or the routing of a polyline. If this value is true then a receiving application should consider the first and last points to be connected.

label: offsetX
comment:
The offset in the X direction. This is used for defining the offset from centre for rendering an icon (the default is that a single point specifies the centre of the icon).

The offset is in per-unit with 0 indicating there is no offset from the horizontal centre of the icon.  -0.5 indicates it is offset by 50% to the left and 0.5 indicates an offset of 50% to the right.

label: offsetY
comment:
The offset in the Y direction. This is used for defining the offset from centre for rendering an icon (the default is that a single point specifies the centre of the icon).

The offset is in per-unit with 0 indicating there is no offset from the vertical centre of the icon.  The offset direction is dependent on the orientation of the diagram, with -0.5 and 0.5 indicating an offset of +/- 50% on the vertical axis.

label: rotation
comment:
Sets the angle of rotation of the diagram object.  Zero degrees is pointing to the top of the diagram.  Rotation is clockwise.  DiagramObject.rotation=0 has the following meaning: The connection point of an element which has one terminal is pointing to the top side of the diagram. The connection point "From side" of an element which has more than one terminal is pointing to the top side of the diagram.
DiagramObject.rotation=90 has the following meaning: The connection point of an element which has one terminal is pointing to the right hand side of the diagram. The connection point "From side" of an element which has more than one terminal is pointing to the right hand side of the diagram.

label: DiagramObjectPoints
comment: A diagram object glue point is associated with 2 or more object points that are considered to be 'glued' together.

label: DiagramObject
comment: The diagram object with which the points are associated.

label: DiagramObjectGluePoint
comment: The 'glue' point to which this point is associated.

label: sequenceNumber
comment: The sequence position of the point, used for defining the order of points for diagram objects acting as a polyline or polygon with more than one point. The attribute shall be a positive value.

label: xPosition
comment: The X coordinate of this point.

label: yPosition
comment: The Y coordinate of this point.

label: zPosition
comment: The Z coordinate of this point.

label: StyledObjects
comment: A style can be assigned to multiple diagram objects.

label: Diagram
comment: A DiagramStyle can be used by many Diagrams.

label: DiagramObjects
comment: The diagram objects that are associated with the domain object.

label: description
comment: The description is a free human readable text describing or naming the object. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

label: mRID
comment:
Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is unique within an exchange context. Global uniqueness is easily achieved by using a UUID, as specified in RFC 4122, for the mRID. The use of UUID is strongly recommended.
For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax conforming to IEC 61970-552, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

label: name
comment: The name is any free human readable and possibly non unique text naming the object.

label: text
comment: The text that is displayed by this text diagram object.

label: VisibleObjects
comment: A visibility layer can contain one or more diagram objects.

label: drawingOrder
comment: The drawing order for this layer.  The higher the number, the later the layer and the objects within it are rendered.
